# Documentation updates (ongoing)

Update docs **in the same work batch** as the code change — not as a separate cleanup later.

## Every user-visible or operational change

When shipping a feature, fix, security patch, or deploy/config change, update:

| File | When |
|------|------|
| **CHANGELOG.md** | Always — under `## Unreleased` until a version bump; then move into the release section |
| **docs/dev-log.md** | Short daily note (Shipped / Fixed / Security / Notes / Next) |
| **README.md** | New or changed user-facing capability — `Implemented` checklist and/or `Current status` table |
| **docs/product-roadmap.md** | Item moved from future → implemented, or scope changed |
| **docs/product-decisions.md** | Rhys locks a new product rule in planning |

Do not wait for a “docs pass”. If the code ships, the docs ship in the same commit or PR.

## README rules

- Stable public-facing information only (positioning, status, high-level feature lists, links).
- Do not bloat with implementation noise or daily notes.
- Do not duplicate full product-decisions or roadmap content.

## What does not need README

Internal refactors, test-only changes, comment edits — unless user-visible.

## Secrets

Never commit secrets or real env values in docs. Use placeholders.

